# Naming Conventions

## General

- Use clear, readable names — avoid abbreviations and technical jargon
- Variables and functions: `camelCase` with descriptive intent
- Types and interfaces: `PascalCase`
- Config constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` (e.g. `FEED_SOURCES`, `CATEGORY_IDS`, `SENTIMENT_KEYWORDS`)

## Files

| Folder | Pattern | Example |
|--------|---------|---------|
| config | `{name}.config.ts` | `feedSources.config.ts` |
| services | `{name}.service.ts` | `newsFeed.service.ts` |
| utils | `{name}.util.ts` | `categoryLookup.util.ts` |
| hooks | `{domain}.hooks.ts` | `articleAnalysis.hooks.ts` |
| contexts | `{Name}Context.tsx` | `NewsFeedContext.tsx` |
| components | `{ComponentName}.tsx` | `CompactArticleCard.tsx` |

## Category IDs

Categories use short string IDs consistently across configs, services, and components:

| ID | Label |
|----|-------|
| `vd` | Vandamme |
| `to` | Tourmaline Oil |
| `iv` | Ivanhoe Mines |
| `ct` | Japanse carry trade |
| `ts` | TSMC |

These IDs are defined in `CATEGORY_IDS` (`feedSources.config.ts`) and used as keys in `TOPIC_KEYWORDS`, `SENTIMENT_KEYWORDS`, CSS theme classes (`.tvd`, `.tto`, etc.), and `categoryId` fields on articles.
